    <persName type="additional" subtype="title">1st marquess of Ripon</persName>
    
    <note type="dates"><date>1827–1909</date></note>
    
    <note type="biography">
        <p>Politician. MP for Huddersfield, 1853–7; for the West Riding, until 1859. A believer in co-operative principles. Helped set up the Working Men’s College in 1854. Earl of Ripon and de Gray, 1859; marquess of Ripon, 1871. A member of William Ewart Gladstone’s cabinet, 1868–73. Viceroy of India, 1880–4.</p></note>
